cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CVPR, cs.GR 

The paper deals with measuring geometric similarity between 3D scenes and associating them, which involves computer vision and robotics (cs.CV and cs.RO). The approach also involves encoding discriminative information in a viewpoint-invariant feature space, which could potentially involve machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions state-of-the-art approaches based on deep learning, which falls under the computer vision and pattern recognition category (cs.CVPR). Finally, the paper discusses how the approach can result in richer 3D reconstructions, which falls under computer graphics (cs.GR).
